post_text:
Freedom Prep Secondary community, CIEE (council for International Educational Exchange) is looking for regular, everyday families to host one or two exchange students for the upcoming school year. One of these students is already in Utah,and can’t wait to be introduced to his permanent host family.

Meet Rodrigo from Spain: . "I’m so excited to begin this new experience with my host family, a new school, new Friends and in the country that I always loved. With your help this will be a great experience to know more your culture and your country. My hobbies are sports like soccer, ski, and swimming and also like to travel, watching Movies, music and TV Shows."

And Dominik from Poland:. I like to discover new places and meet new people. I like to help in home activities. I like animals (currently I have a cat, I used to have turtle and mouse). I love to do sports activities, especially play soccer.

These boys are so excited to learn about the culture here in America. Contact us to learn more or to include him in your family this year.

post_text: The inscription on one gravestone in the Allied Cemetery in Germany to honor those who fought in World War ll reads: “He was one of many, but he was our only son." On this day, we honor our country which was founded to give liberty and justice for all - and to those who have fought to to preserve that freedom. With all of our hearts, we thank you for your service.

post_text: Our Provo elementary campus has been collecting items for refugees in Salt Lake. The student council planned and executed the whole thing. One of our 5th graders had the idea and the vision. As a school, we collected over $1,200 worth of supplies which included diapers, wipes, socks, cleaning supplies, snacks, paper towels and toilet paper. We were able to drop off bags to about 50 different families in need. #FPAProvo

post_text: Nutrition Matters at Freedom Prep. Meet Dr. April Dean, our Director of Nutrition. Her resume includes a doctorate degree, faculty member at Brigham Young University, and nutritious meal prepping skills that are sure to make any kids taste buds go wild. On top of that, Dr. April Dean is focused on buying local produce from local farms and creating a meal program that builds passion for health in the children here at FPA.
